@database "Search & Replace Guide"
@author "Heiko Schr—der"
@$VER: 3.0 (Release 3)
@wordwrap

@node Main "Search & Replace V2.1"
                               @{" < Table of contents " link "Macro-Package.guide/Main"}

@{fg shine}Benifits:@{fg text}
   Search and replace, dependent on font, is usually not possible. However this
   macro can distinguish between data in different Typefaces and Font sizes.

@{fg shine}Requirements:@{fg text}
   A Font Code list. See @{"FontLook" link "FontLook.guide/main"}.

@{fg shine}Using the @{"macro" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview SearchNReplace.iff"}:@{fg text}

   Search for
   @{fg fill}W@{fg text}hat
      Here you place the string for which you are searching.
      Naturally you can also look fo the next occurance of the string.

   S@{fg fill}p@{fg text}ecs
      Here you choose the font which the string must be in.
      The Search-next is also Font sensitive.
      If you do not set a specification, the whole text will be searched

   Replace by
   Wha@{fg fill}t@{fg text}
      Works the same as normal.
      You give it the string or word to replace the original.

   Sp@{fg fill}e@{fg text}cs
      You can select a typeface or font style to use with the replaced text.

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

   @{fg fill}S@{fg text}earch
      The search for the string will begin.

   @{fg fill}R@{fg text}eplace
      Replace the next found string that fulfills all the requirements.


   @{fg fill}A@{fg text}ll
      Search and replace all of the strings in the document that fulfill
      the criteria.

   @{fg fill}ESC@{fg text} or closing the window
      Terminates the macro.

@endnode
